Cell["\<\
There is a relationship between \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]AnnouncementTiming\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]DaysToAnnouncement\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] (also visible in the correlation matrix below) which \
was expected and is, why I planned to only include one of the two from the \
start. \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]DaysToAnnouncement\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] only \
exists in the dataset as a backup, in case \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]AnnouncementTiming\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] cannot be \
used as an explanatory variable for some reason.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8678464068877974`*^9, 3.867846516426312*^9}, {
  3.867913135939251*^9, 
  3.867913184843172*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"95b8287e-787b-465f-bed8-\
c102e3db9df0"],

Cell["\<\
No obvious patterns indicating a non-linear relationship are visible. The \
relationships between the dependent variable and the explanatory variables \
mostly seem to be quite weak.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8678464068877974`*^9, 3.867846516426312*^9}, {
  3.867913135939251*^9, 3.86791316854832*^9}, {3.867913207627496*^9, 
  3.8679133249294863`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ee7baebe-805d-4ca3-a130-\
cb9cda817b70"]
}, Open  ]],

